Avian influenza situation in Indonesia -- WHO update
----------------------------------------------------
The Indonesian IHR National Focal Point of the Ministry of Health has notified the WHO of a new case of human infection with avian influenza A(H5N1) virus.

The case is a 2-year-old male from Riau Province. He developed fever on 17 Apr 2012 and was hospitalized on 21 Apr 2012 but he died on 27 Apr 2012.

Epidemiological investigation is ongoing. Preliminary findings indicate that the patient's parents are quail egg vendors.

The case was confirmed by the National Institute of Health Research and Development (NIHRD), Ministry of Health.

To date, of the 189 cases reported in Indonesia since 2005, 157 have been fatal.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail Rapporteur Marianne Hopp

[This is the WHO confirmation of the fatal case of avian influenza virus infection in Riau province reported in a previous ProMED post (Avian influenza, human (49): Indonesia (RU) child 20120502.1120713). No further information is provided regarding the circumstances of the child's exposure.

This WHO confirmation is posted, although it adds no new information, because many suspected human cases of avian influenza virus infection in Indonesia are never officially confirmed.

Riau is a province of Indonesia located in the center of the island of Sumatra. The capital and the largest city is Pekanbaru. The interactive HealthMap of Riau province can be accessed at: http://healthmap.org/r/2iLo. - Mod.CP]
